<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-09T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-09T09:00:00-05:00" n="15" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d15">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/5–949: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Baruch</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-09T15:00:00+01:00">May 9,
                                    1949—3 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received May 9—2:55 p. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>390. Discussed Foreign Minister Depcirtel May 8 [<hi rend="italic">6</hi>], 5 p. m. anent China and on both points 1 and 2, he expressed
                            entire cooperation and agreement.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Baruch</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
